Comment: races per circuit confused here are the f rules On Friday drivers have a minute free practice session and a minute qualifying session The qualifying session decides the grid order for Saturday s race which has a length of kilometres miles During Saturday s race Feature Race each driver must complete one compulsory pitstop and must use at least one set of each specification of dry weather tyres Sunday s race Sprint Race is run over kilometres miles The grid is decided by the Saturday result with top being reversed so the driver who finished th on Saturday will start from pole position and the winner will start from th place The exceptions to these rules are the Monaco and Budapest where the Feature Race is run over km miles and km miles respectively and the Monaco Sprint Race where the race is run over km miles

Comment: Imagine if the season s reviews of the s had used the standard we use today to judge the races Annnnd the first dull race of the season Oh another dull race Oh another dull race Oh wow an actual close race I think a lot of the same people who complain about this modern Formula in a way are the total representation of the modern Formula fan They demand tenth of a second finished each race A driver who wins in dominant form Boring it is a shame Formula is broken they shout Where is the romance the spirit in that attitude The same people decrying artificial Mario Kart racing decry every real race that isn t artificially close as boring dull a wast of time etc Some of the greatest drives in history have been total dominations by drivers who on that day in that place were in a class of its own Sure it s not a photo finish but racing is about driving and winning not artificially making things close for fans who on the one hand decry all change but on the other hand demand massive changes to change the fundamentals of F to make it more exciting F racing is massively closer today than it was back in its hey day It is less competitive in the sense that less teams can actually win but nonetheless the cars are closer together I would not want to watch a top racing series where a driver who utterly out performs his teammate and his opponents and wins by a big margin is somehow looked up as dull boring and a waste of time I don t only watch racing for the rare ultra close photo finish I also watch it for the sake of driving cars teams etc Even a dominant win is still never a gurantee My only point is that fans and the culture around F have become so intensely focused on entertainment and close racing that they miss the forest for the trees It takes all the fun out of to micro analyze everything Watch a season review and look at how many dull races there were by today s standards AND YET all of today s modern fans say things like It was so much better back then It sucks now But the at the same time anytime there is a race similar to races of the s they say boring Lol
